\
This is what they call agentic coding.\
\
[PAUSE]\
\
Here's what that actually means. The old AI coding assistants were stateless. You'd highlight a function, say "fix this," and it would spit out a fix. One and done. No memory. No follow-through.\
\
[ON-SCREEN TEXT: OLD WAY = Stateless \'95 No Memory \'95 One-Shot Fixes]\
